parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A stuck caliper can cause the brake rotor to wear unevenly, leading to premature wear and potentially causing accidents.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The premature failure of brake components, such as rotors, calipers, and lines, can lead to reduced braking performance and increased stopping distances, potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: and lines need to be replaced frequently
and the vehicle may exhibit unusual brake noise or vibration.

symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brakes do not engage properly

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Anti-lock Braking System (ABS) can cause the vehicle to skid or lose control, potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: The ABS system does not activate

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brakes to slow or stop the vehicle can lead to extended stopping distances and potentially cause accidents.
symptoms: The brakes take longer than usual to slow or stop the vehicle
